&lt;li&gt;Manage Accounts Receivable (AR), including issuing customer invoices and monitoring collections.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage Accounts Payable (AP), including processing and posting supplier invoices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Record and reconcile bank transactions and cash movements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze financial data for accuracy and compliance.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure timely and accurate accounting of tax information from tax department.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor account balances and resolve discrepancies.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform detailed account reconciliations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in preparing budget variances.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support internal and external audits.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement improvements to accounting processes and systems.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay updated on relevant accounting regulations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Train and mentor junior accounting staff.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
